HEADWORD: Shyster
<hw>Shy"ster</hw> <pr>(?)</pr>, <pos>n.</pos> <ety>[Perh. from G.
<ets>scheisse</ets> excrement.]</ety> <def>A trickish knave; one who
carries on any business, especially legal business, in a mean and
dishonest way.</def> <mark>[Slang, U.S.]</mark>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

